        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:09:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nActually no. What this role does should be put in test/roles/prepare-rke. As we agreed in doc roles in test/roles should have name '<stage>-<role name>' and we don't have \"docker-dind\" role. And what's more rke role is the only place we're gonna use it.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d8662b7127ceb7f51180a9550ca84d0d7f45bab9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:11:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "73a589176ecf8c0ab246a9c38296dabff5237ed3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5019,
          "name": "Michal Zegan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "m.zegan@samsung.com",
          "username": "m.zegan"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:17:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwell no. this role is meant to replace prepare-docker in the long run, or it is at least a proposal/alternative implementation without destroying prepare-docker and other tests using it. I believe that either prepare-docker and this role should be merged, or if there are any objections on how this role works and good reasoning for how prepare-docker works, rke role should use prepare-docker instead. In case it is unclean, both could coexist for some time. But it is definitely not meant to be rke specific.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "03569004e4eabd61f214e38cd8d39fc68b64f7f1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5019,
          "name": "Michal Zegan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "m.zegan@samsung.com",
          "username": "m.zegan"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:19:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nmain reason for me not to use the original prepare-docker is that it uses host docker so I would need to manually clean up images... and that is error prone. this reasoning applies to all other roles using prepare-docker.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "faf33ed4777599322a6b04e659dd90942e9da6d2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5019,
