        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:26:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI haven't seen any task on Jira with a description/proposal of an initiative to rework prepare-docker role in a way that all tests will utilize DinD. Without a task/epic for that it won't happen unless you're driver for that?\n\nSo if that is the case please raise appropriate tasks on Jira, otherwise it won't happen unless you're on the track with refactoring all tests to use dind which i haven't heard of.\n\n\"prepare-docker\" role has much more functionality than what's in this commit.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8039dce2ccce15ffd4823dc4c147a65901689591",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5019,
          "name": "Michal Zegan",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "m.zegan@samsung.com",
          "username": "m.zegan"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-14 14:30:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I haven't seen any task on Jira with a description/proposal of an\n > initiative to rework prepare-docker role in a way that all tests\n > will utilize DinD. Without a task/epic for that it won't happen\n > unless you're driver for that?\n > \n > So if that is the case please raise appropriate tasks on Jira,\n > otherwise it won't happen unless you're on the track with\n > refactoring all tests to use dind which i haven't heard of.\n > \n > \"prepare-docker\" role has much more functionality than what's in\n > this commit.\n\nWell, I just quickly made a separate role because it was nicer for me than writing cleanup playbook that would require careful collecting of image names and such like. however you are right that making a dind version of prepare-docker as the only option would require modifications to all other roles and would varrant a new task. I can be a driver for that, however not sure what should be the next steps in this specific case.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
